<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-30T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Sm 61/184: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-30T22:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">December 30,
                                        1921—10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 3, 1922—1:43
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1. Your 354, December 21 [<hi rend="italic">20</hi>], 6 p.m. I have been
                            granted provisional recognition by the Hungarian Government as Chargé
                            d’Affaires as from December 26th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>